cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.DS, cs.CY, cs.DB

The paper compares citation counts from different databases, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are likely because they deal with information retrieval and analysis. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DB (Databases) are also possible because they involve data management and analysis. Finally, cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a possibility because the paper discusses research evaluation, which is relevant to the social implications of computing.
